         <abstract>
            <p>Continuing the recent work of the second author, we prove that the diophantine equation f&lt;sub&gt;a&lt;/sub&gt;(x, y) = x&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; - ax&lt;sup&gt;3y&lt;/sup&gt; - x&lt;sup&gt;2y&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + axy&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; + y&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; = 1 for |a| ≥ 3 has exactly 12 solutions except when |a| = 4, when it has 16 solutions. If α = α(a) denotes one of the zeros of f&lt;sub&gt;a&lt;/sub&gt;(x, 1), then for |a| ≥ 4 we also find all γ ∈ Z[ α ] with Z[ γ ] = Z[ α ].</p>
          </abstract>
